{"parse":{"title":"mentor","pageid":76323,"redirects":[],"wikitext":"{{also|Mentor}}\n==English==\n{{wp}}\n\n===Etymology===\n{{root|en|ine-pro|*men- (think)}}\nFrom {{der|en|fr|mentor}}, from {{der|en|grc|Μέντωρ||Mentor}}, a mythological character in the [[w:Odyssey|Odyssey]], whose name, a historical name from Ancient Greece, shares the same root as English [[mind#English|mind]].<ref>\"mentor, n.\". OED Online. March 2013. Oxford University Press. 1 April 2013, http://www.oed.com/view/Entry/116575?rskey=EAtx24&result=1&isAdvanced=false.</ref> Cognate to {{cog|sa|मन्तृ||advisor, counselor}} and {{cog|la|monitor||one who admonishes}}, and perhaps ultimately from {{der|en|ine-pro|*monéyeti}} (compare {{cog|la|moneō|t=to warn}}, causative form of {{m|ine-pro|*men-||to think}}.<ref>{{R:Etymonline}}</ref>\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{enPR|men'tôr|men'tər}}\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈmɛn.tɔː/|/ˈmɛn.toə/|a=RP|a2=non-horse-hoarse}}\n** {{audio|en|LL-Q1860 (eng)-Vealhurl-mentor.wav|a=Southern England}}\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈmɛn.toɹ/|/ˈmɛn.tɚ/|a=GA,CA}}\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈmen.toː/|a=AU,NZ}}\n* {{rhymes|en|ɛntə(ɹ)|ɛntɔː(ɹ)|s1=2}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{en-noun}}\n\n# A [[wise]] and [[trusted]] [[counselor]] or [[teacher]].\n#* {{quote-text|en|year=2006|author=Lisa Johnson|title=Mind Your X's and Y's\n|passage=Many '''mentors''' claim that they would work with the vocationers for free because of the sense of satisfaction the interaction provides.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=2009|author=w:Reif Larsen|title=The Selected Works of T.S. Spivet|publisher=Pinguin Books|page=26\n|passage=I thought he was supposed to be my '''mentor'''. But, in actuality, what did I know about the often beguiling world of adults?}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col|en|mentee|mentoree|mentorial|mentorish|mentorism|mentorless|mentorlike|mentorly|mentorship|telementor\n|e-mentor|e-mentorship|mentorship|{{l|en|mentoress}}, {{l|en|mentress}}|mentrix}}\n\n====Translations====\n{{trans-top|wise and trusted counselor or teacher}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t+|bg|наставник|m}}, {{t|bg|ментор|m}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Mandarin: {{t+|cmn|指導者|tr=zhǐdǎozhě}}, {{t+|cmn|導師|tr=dǎoshī}}\n* Danish: {{t|da|mentor|c}}\n* Dutch: [[mentor#Dutch|mentor]] {{g|m}}, {{t+|nl|leidsman|m}}\n* Esperanto: {{t|eo|mentoro}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|ohjaaja}}, {{t|fi|oppi-isä}}, {{t+|fi|mentori}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|mentor|m}}\n* German: {{t+|de|Mentor|m}}, {{t+|de|Vertrauensperson|f}}, {{t|de|Vertrauenslehrer|m}}\n* Greek: {{t+|el|μέντορας|m}}\n* Gujarati: {{t|gu|શિક્ષક}}\n* Hebrew: {{t+|he|מַנְחֶה|m|tr=manẖé}}, {{t|he|חוֹנֵךְ|m|tr=ẖonéch}}\n* Hindi: {{t+|hi|मार्गदर्शक|m}}\n* Indonesian: {{t+|id|mentor}}, {{t+|id|pembimbing}}\n* Italian: {{t+|it|mentore|m}}, {{t+|it|pigmalione|m}}, {{t+|it|tutore|m}}\n* Japanese: {{t+|ja|メンター|tr=mentā}}\n* Korean: {{t|ko|멘토}}\n* Macedonian: {{t+|mk|у́чител|m}}, {{t|mk|ме́нтор|m}}, {{t|mk|воспи́тувач|m}}\n* Mari:\n*: Eastern Mari: {{t|mhr|ача}}\n* Portuguese: {{t+|pt|mentor|m}}\n* Russian: {{t+|ru|наста́вник|m}}, {{t+|ru|ме́нтор|m}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|mentor|m}}\n* Swedish: {{t+|sv|mentor|c}}\n* Turkish: {{t+|tr|hoca|n}}\n* Welsh: {{t|cy|mentor}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n===Verb===\n{{en-verb}}\n\n# {{lb|en|transitive}} To [[act]] as someone's mentor.\n#* {{quote-journal\n|en\n|date=2008-09-08\n|author=Richard Halloran\n|coauthors=\n|title=Japan’s rapid succession of prime ministers belies its global role\n|newspaper=Taipei Times\n|location=Taipai\n|publisher=\n|quotee=\n|url=http://www.taipeitimes.com/News/editorials/archives/2008/09/08/2003422576\n|page=9\n|passage=After him came several deshi, or followers he had '''mentored'''.\n}}\n#* {{quote-journal|en|journal=Time|title=Soledad O'Brien: We Should Rethink What '''Mentoring''' Means|author=Soledad O'Brien|date=16-09-2016\n|passage=I want to get people motivated about '''mentoring''' students, to help them get excited about staying in school, finding their passion, and starting a career.\n|url=https://time.com/4495903/soledad-obrien-mentor-advice/}}\n\n====Translations====\n{{trans-top|to act as someone's mentor}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t+|bg|наставлявам}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|opastaa}}, {{t+|fi|ohjata}}, {{t|fi|mentoroida}}\n* German: {{t+|de|betreuen}}\n* Serbo-Croatian: {{t|sh|mentorirati}}, {{t|sh|mentorisati}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n===Related terms===\n* {{l|en|mentee}}\n\n===See also===\n{{col4|en\n|coach\n|nestor\n|sponsor\n}}\n\n===References===\n<references/>\n\n===Further reading===\n* [http://www.languagehat.com/archives/003341.php Article on the etymology and history of the word “mentor” on languagehat.com]\n\n===Anagrams===\n* {{anagrams|en|a=emnort|Morten|meront|termon|Ermont|montre|Merton|Monter|tormen|Termon|metron}}\n\n{{cln|en|eponyms}}\n{{C|en|People}}\n\n==Cebuano==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{root|ceb|ine-pro|*men- (think)}}\nFrom {{der|ceb|en|mentor}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{hyph|ceb|men|tor}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|ceb|noun}}\n\n# {{l|en|mentor}} {{gl|a [[wise]] and [[trusted]] [[counselor]] or [[teacher]]}}\n#* '''2019''' — Ciar, Troy, ''[https://www.sunstar.com.ph/ampArticle/1831801 Super Ka: Aida Patana Mikulit og Kasaysayan sa Mrs. Philippines World]'' (13 November), SuperBalita\n#*: {{quote|ceb|\"She may speak nonsense sometimes but she’s a very hardworking woman,” matod pa sa iyang giisip nga '''mentor''' ug amahan nga si Senyorito Michel Lhuillier atol sa thanksgiving ug send-off party ug birthday celebration niya niadtong Dominggo.}}\n\n===Verb===\n{{head|ceb|verb}}\n\n# to act as a mentor\n\n{{cln|ceb|terms derived from French|terms derived from Ancient Greek|eponyms}}\n{{C|ceb|People}}\n\n==Danish==\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{der|da|grc|Μέντωρ||Mentor}}, a mythological character in the [[w:Odyssey|Odyssey]].\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|da|/mɛntər/|[ˈmɛntˢɐ]}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{da-noun|en|er}}\n\n# {{l|en|mentor}}\n\n====Inflection====\n{{da-noun-infl|en|er}}\n\n====Synonyms====\n* {{l|da|læremester}}\n* {{l|da|vejleder}}\n\n====Further reading====\n* {{pedia|lang=da}}\n\n==Dutch==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{bor+|nl|fr|mentor}}, from {{der|nl|grc|Μέντωρ}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|nl|/ˈmɛn.tɔr/}}\n* {{audio|nl|Nl-mentor.ogg}}\n* {{hyph|nl|men|tor}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{nl-noun|m|-s,-:en|+|f=mentrix}}\n\n# a {{l|en|mentor}}, wise/grey [[adviser]], [[tutor]] etc.\n\n====Synonyms====\n* {{l|nl|raadsman|g=m}}\n* {{l|nl|leidsman|g=m}}, {{l|nl|gids}} {{g2|m}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n* {{l|nl|mentorspan|g=n}}\n\n====Descendants====\n* {{desc|id|mentor|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|pap|mèntòr|bor=1}}\n\n==French==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{ety|fr|:bor|grc:Μέντωρ}}\n{{bor+|fr|grc|Μέντωρ}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{fr-IPA|mɑ̃.tɔʁ|mɛ̃.tɔʁ}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{fr-noun|m}}\n\n# {{l|en|mentor}}, [[guide]]\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:fr:TLFi}}\n\n===Anagrams===\n* {{l|fr|monter}}\n* {{l|fr|montre}}, {{l|fr|montré}}\n\n==Indonesian==\n{{wp|id:}}\n\n===Etymology===\n{{bor+|id|nl|mentor}}, from {{der|id|fr|mentor}}, from {{der|id|grc|Μέντωρ}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{id-pr|mèn.tor}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{id-noun}}\n\n# {{lb|id|education}} {{l|en|mentor}}\n#: {{syn|id|pembimbing|pengasuh}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col|id\n|mementori\n|dimentori\n|pementoran\n}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:KBBI Daring}}\n\n==Norwegian Bokmål==\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{der|nb|grc|Μέντωρ||Mentor}}.\n\n===Noun===\n{{nb-noun-m1}}\n\n# a {{l|en|mentor}}\n\n===References===\n* {{R:nb:OB}}\n\n==Polish==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{ety|pl|:lbor|grc:Μέντωρ|text=+|tree=1}}\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{pl-pr|a=Pl-mentor.ogg}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{pl-noun|m-pr|f=mentorka|adj=mentorski}}\n\n# {{lb|pl|literary}} {{l|en|mentor}} {{gl|wise and trusted counselor or teacher}}\n#: {{syn|pl|nauczyciel|wychowawca}}\n# {{lb|pl|derogatory|or|ironic}} [[moralist]], [[moralizer]]\n#: {{syn|pl|kaznodzieja|moralista|moralizator|rezoner}}\n\n====Declension====\n{{pl-decl-noun-m-pr|nomp=mentorzy/mentorowie}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col|pl|title=nouns|mentorstwo}}\n{{col|pl|title=verbs|mentorować}}\n\n====Related terms====\n{{col|pl|title=nouns|mentoring}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:pl:WSJP}}\n* {{R:pl:PWN}}\n\n{{C|pl|Male people}}\n\n==Portuguese==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{pt-IPA|mentôr}}\n* {{hyph|pt|men|tor}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{pt-noun|m|f=+}}\n\n# {{l|en|mentor}} {{gloss|a wise and trusted counsellor or teacher}}\n\n====Related terms====\n* {{l|pt|mente}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:pt:Aulete}}\n* {{R:pt:Priberam}}\n\n==Romanian==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{bor+|ro|fr|mentor}}, from {{der|ro|la|mentor}}.\n\n===Noun===\n{{ro-noun|m|mentori}}\n\n# {{l|en|mentor}}\n\n====Declension====\n{{ro-noun-m}}\n\n==Spanish==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{bor+|es|grc|Μέντωρ||Mentor}}, a mythological character in the [[w:Odyssey|Odyssey]], whose name, a historical name from Ancient Greece may share the same root as English {{m|en|mind}}, would mean that ''mentor'' ultimately descends from the Proto-Indo-European root {{m|ine-pro|*men-|id=think}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{es-pr}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{es-noun|m|f=+}}\n\n# {{l|en|mentor}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col|es|mentoría}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:es:DRAE}}\n\n==Swedish==\n\n===Noun===\n{{sv-noun|c}}\n\n# A {{l|en|mentor}}\n\n====Declension====\n{{sv-infl-noun-c-er|sg-nom-def=mentorn|sg-gen-def=mentorns}}\n\n===Anagrams===\n* {{anagrams|sv|a=emnort|monter}}\n\n==Vietnamese==\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{bor|vi|en|mentor}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{vi-IPA|men tờ}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{vi-noun}}\n\n# [[#English|mentor]]\n#: {{uxi|vi|tìm '''mentor'''|to find a '''mentor'''}}\n\n==Welsh==\n\n===Etymology===\nBorrowed from {{bor|cy|en|mentor}}.\n\n===Noun===\n{{cy-noun|m|mentoriaid}}\n\n# [[#English|mentor]]\n\n===Mutation===\n{{cy-mut}}\n\n===References===\n* {{R:cy:GPC}}\n* [http://www.bbc.co.uk/cgi-bin/wales/learnwelsh/welsh_dictionary.pl?i=c&gair=mentor&Chwilio=Search Definition of 'mentor' from the BBC].\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20070623131726/http://www.mentors.ca/contestquestion.html Alternative definition of the source of 'mentor' from Peer Resources].\n\n{{topics|cy|People}}"}}